.TH MD-TO-PDF 1 "June 2026" "pandoc-wrapper 1.0.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
md-to-pdf \- convert Markdown to a branded PDF via Pandoc and XeLaTeX
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B md-to-pdf
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.IR "markdown-file(s) | directory | URL"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B md-to-pdf
turns Markdown with YAML front matter into a styled, branded PDF. It merges a
brand configuration with the document, runs Pandoc with a Lua filter (special
boxes, styled datatables, charts) and an Eisvogel-based LaTeX template, and
produces a PDF with XeLaTeX.
.PP
Multiple input files are concatenated in order; a directory is searched for
.I .md
and
.I .yaml
files; an http(s) URL is downloaded first.
.SH FORMATS
A document selects its output format with the
.B template:
field in its front matter; a brand provides the default. All formats share
the brand system (colours, fonts, identity).
.TP
.B report
The default (\fBeisvogel-wrapper\fR, or the minimal \fBmvp\fR): title page, table
of contents and styled body \- reports, briefings and policy documents.
.TP
.B letter
.RB "(" "template: letter" ")."
No title page; the recipient address
.RB "(" to: ", a list of lines)"
is positioned for a DL window envelope, with the date and optional
.BR our-ref / your-ref
on the right, an optional bold
.B subject
and optional
.BR opening / closing / signature .
A letterhead is either a full-page
.B letterhead:
artwork, or built from
.BR letterhead-logo ", " letterhead-company " and " letterhead-contact
(a ruled logo-and-contact footer).
.TP
.B slides (beamer)
.RB "(" "template: beamer" ")."
A beamer slide deck. Standard beamer
.BR theme ", " colortheme " and " fonttheme
are honoured, and the brand palette is wired into the beamer colours via the
brand's
.BR beamer-structure / beamer-accent .
Selecting it switches the output to Pandoc's beamer writer.
.TP
.B slides (modern)
.RB "(" "template: slides" ")."
A flat, full-bleed slide deck rendered in pure XeLaTeX (not beamer): solid
brand-colour grounds, bold type, and auto-boxed images. A level-1 heading is a
section/divider slide, a level-2 heading a content slide; the per-slide colour
role is set with an
.RB "{." light / dark / accent "}"
heading attribute. Grounds default from the brand's
.BR beamer-structure / beamer-accent
and are overridable per deck with
.BR slide-title-bg / slide-accent .
.PP
Full field lists and worked examples are in the authoring guide (see
.BR FILES ).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-order\-alpha
Sort multiple input files alphabetically before concatenating.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Print verbose debug output.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-viewer
Do not open the PDF viewer after a successful build.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a help summary (including the resolved paths) and exit.
.SH BRANDS
A document selects a brand in its front matter:
.PP
.RS
.B brand:
.I name
.RE
.PP
.B plain
is the default brand and ships with the tool. Your own brands live in an
external base folder, one subfolder per brand:
.PP
.RS
.IR <base> / <name> /template.yaml
.RE
.PP
together with that brand's assets (for example
.IR logo.png ,
.IR cover.pdf ).
Assets are referenced by
.B bare filename
in
.IR template.yaml ;
the build adds the brand folder to Pandoc's
.B \-\-resource\-path
and to
.B TEXINPUTS
so they resolve. A brand is therefore self\-contained and portable \- it can
live in its own repository or package.
.PP
The brands base is resolved in this order:
.IP 1. 3
the
.B MD_TO_PDF_BRANDS
environment variable;
.IP 2. 3
the
.B brands_dir
setting in the configuration file (see below);
.IP 3. 3
the bundled default brand
.RB ( plain ),
which is always available as a fallback.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is read from
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/pandoc-wrapper/config
(by default
.IR ~/.config/pandoc-wrapper/config ),
or from the path in
.BR MD_TO_PDF_CONFIG .
It uses simple
.I key = value
lines. The key that matters is the brands base:
.PP
.RS
.B brands_dir =
.I /path/to/your/brands
.RE
.PP
A leading
.B ~
is expanded to your home directory. When no brands base is configured,
.B md-to-pdf
uses the bundled
.B plain
brand and prints a one\-line hint on each run.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/pandoc-wrapper/config
Per\-user configuration (\fBbrands_dir\fR).
.TP
.I /usr/share/pandoc-wrapper/templates/
LaTeX templates, the shared preamble and the Lua filter.
.TP
.I /usr/share/pandoc-wrapper/brands/plain/
The bundled default brand.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MD_TO_PDF_BRANDS
Override the brands base folder.
.TP
.B MD_TO_PDF_TEMPLATES
Override the templates folder.
.TP
.B MD_TO_PDF_CONFIG
Override the configuration file path.
.TP
.B MD_TO_PDF_VIEWER
PDF viewer to open on success (default
.IR /usr/bin/evince ).
.SH EXAMPLES
Build a document with the default brand:
.PP
.RS
.B md-to-pdf report.md
.RE
.PP
Configure your own brands once, then use them:
.PP
.RS
.B mkdir -p ~/.config/pandoc-wrapper
.br
.B echo 'brands_dir = ~/pandoc-brands' > ~/.config/pandoc-wrapper/config
.br
.B md-to-pdf --no-viewer report.md
.RE
.PP
Create a new brand by copying the default:
.PP
.RS
.B cp -r /usr/share/pandoc-wrapper/brands/plain ~/pandoc-brands/acme
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pandoc (1),
.BR xelatex (1).
Full authoring and template documentation is installed under
.IR /usr/share/doc/pandoc-wrapper/ .
.SH AUTHOR
Stuart J Mackintosh <sjm@opendigital.cc>
